## Why Students Need a Credit Card

Building credit early gives you a head start on major milestones: renting an apartment, financing a car, or getting approved for competitive jobs that check credit (yes, employers look).

**The stats:**
- 73% of employers check credit for some positions
- 87% of landlords run credit checks
- Average credit score at age 25: 659 (needs work)

Starting at 18-22 with a student card can boost your score to 700+ by graduation—putting you ahead of peers.

