## Common Questions

**Can I get a student card with no income?**
You need some income (including regular parental support). Scholarships and financial aid count under CARD Act.

**Will applying hurt my credit?**
Initial application = hard inquiry (-5 to -10 points temporarily). Score recovers in 3-6 months with responsible use.

**Should I ask my parents to cosign?**
No need for student cards—they're designed for limited/no credit history. Avoid cosigning (it complicates credit building).

**What if I'm denied?**
- Try Discover it Secured (deposit-based)
- Become authorized user on parent's card (builds history without responsibility)
- Wait 6 months, reapply with higher income

